imum|Ad Decimum, Battle of]] * [[Adelchis of Benevento]] * [[Pope Adeodatus I|Adeodatus I, Pope of Rome]] * [[Pope Adeodatus II|Adeodatus II, Pope of Rome]] * [[Adergoudounbades]]m * [[Adolius]] * [[Adralestos (Domestic of the Schools)]] * [[Adramyttium]] * [[Pope Adrian I|Adrian I, Pope of Rome]] * [[Pope Adrian II|Adrian II, Pope of Rome]] * [[Edirne|Adrianople]] * [[Battle of Adrianople|Adrianople, 378 Battle of]] * [[Siege of Adrianople (813)|Adrianople, 813 Siege of]] * [[Battle of Adrianople (1205)|Adrianople, 1205 Battle of]] * [[Battle of Adrianople (1254)|Adrianople, 1254 Battle of]] * [[Conquest of Adrianople by the Turks|Adrianople, Conquest by the Turks]] * [[Martyrs of Adrianople|Adrianople, Martyrs of]] * [[Adrianos Komnenos]] * [[Aedesia]] * [[Aegean Sea]] * [[Aegean Sea (theme)]] * [[Aelia Eudocia]] * [[Aelia Eudoxia]] * [[Aelia Flaccilla]] * [[Aetios (eunuch)]] * [[Cistern of Aetius|Aetius, Cistern of]] * [[Aetius (praetorian prefect)]] * [[Aëtius of Amida]] * [[Praetorian prefecture of Africa|Africa, Praetorian prefecture of]] * [[Agallianos Kontoskeles]] * [[Agapetus (deacon)]] * [[Agapius (physician)]] * [[Agatha (wife of Samuel of Bulgaria)]] * [[Agathias]] * [[Pope Agatho|Agatho, Pope of Rome]] * [[Agilulf]] * [[Agnellus, Bishop of Ravenna]] * [[Agnes of France, Byzantine Empress]] * [[Agnes of Montferrat]] * [[Agnes of Durazzo]] * [[Ahmad ibn Kayghalagh]] * [[Ahmad ibn Tughan al-Ujayfi]] * [[AIMA prophecy]] * [[Aistulf]] * [[Aiulf II of Benevento]] * [[Aizanoi]] * [[Battle of Ajnadayn|Ajnadayn, Battle of]] * [[Akakia]] * [[Akameros]] * [[Akolouthos]] * [[Barony of Akova|Akova, Barony of]] * [[Akritai]] * [[Battle of Akroinon|Akroinon, Battle of]] * [[Alahan Monastery]] * [[Alamanikon]] * [[Alan Cameron (classical scholar)]] * [[Alans]] * [[Albania in the Middle Ages]] * [[Albania under the Byzantine Empire]] * [[Timeline of Albanian history|Albanian history, Timeline of]] * [[Albia Dominica]] * [[Alboin]] * [[Albsuinda]] * [[Alda of Alania]] *